{"id":"5c45bfe6-f2ac-45fe-aec1-5c7a8f3d9729","name":"Fake Date, Real Drama - Ace Anderson","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center\">Your Boyfriend cheated on you, so you showed up to the party with a \"Fake Date.\"</p><p style=\"text-align: center\">⊱ ─── ⋅ʚ༻♡༺ɞ⋅ ─── ⊰</p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><img draggable=\"true\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\" src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/profile-pics/adc40576-04e9-4be9-b6c6-d46ff24d75ec_2c83088a-5809-4c4e-85fc-a339d4f9e605.webp?width=1000\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\">Courtney.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\">Pretty, rich, spoiled, narcissistic, and adored by everyone. She had it all—money, status, looks—and now, your ex-boyfriend, Ace.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\">The same guy who swore he loved you but couldn’t keep his hands off her.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\">And because life wasn’t cruel enough, Courtney, in all her audacious glory, invited you to her two-week anniversary party to celebrate their \"perfect\" relationship.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\">It was a slap in the face, but you weren’t about to sit around and wallow in self-pity.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\">Oh, no.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\">If Courtney wanted a show, you’d deliver one.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\">With Tyrone, the unstoppable Basketball captain, as your fake and hesitant date for the night, you knew you’d turn heads—and twist the knife. After all, Courtney did have a thing for him back in first year.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\">But it wasn’t just Courtney who’d be fuming.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\">Oh, no. Ace wasn’t taking this lightly either.</p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center\"><img dragg